fields.Title: YARD / PILE OF ETERNITE
fields.Description: Someone has left some crumbly looking eternite panels leaning against this wall. Most suspicious.

fields.Title: Pile of Eternite: "An inconspicuous pile of the roofin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An inconspicuous pile of the roofing material, eternite.
fields.Alternate1: The pile of eternite looks stranger now that Cuno told you about his... pad.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "There it is! You see a shabby littl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There it is! You see a shabby little door.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "It reveals no secrets at this time."
fields.Dialogue Text: It reveals no secrets at this time.

fields.Title: You: "Why am I looking at this pile of th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why am I looking at this pile of the roofing material?
fields.tooltip2: Cuno told you about his shack.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Pile of Eternite: "An inconspicuous pile of the roofin..."]
Inland Empire: "Hard to say, it's gone now. Feeling..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hard to say, it's gone now. Feelings pass, you see. Especially the small ones.

fields.Title: Pile of Eternite: "It's nothing. Someone just left som..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's nothing. Someone just left some roofing material slanted against an old shack.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Glad you asked. When junior researc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Glad you asked. When junior researcher Õlari Taal invented eternite in the Värtna Polytechnic Institute, some thirty odd years ago, he thought it would last forever -- hence the name eternite. Sadly the only lasting thing turned out to be the material's highly carcinogenic effect.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Rhythmic pattern -- calms your mind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Rhythmic pattern -- calms your mind. Mammals like this stuff.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Because there's a secret door hidde..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because there's a secret door hidden behind the panels of eternite. That's why they're *too* orderly.
fields.Alternate1: Because unless Cuno lied, you should just be able to pull the panels aside.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What is this, then? A tool shed?"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is this, then? A tool shed?" He peeks inside. "Let's investigate."
fields.Alternate1: "So this is the shack Cuno mentioned... Let's take a look inside, then."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "No, there's more to this. You get t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, there's more to this. You get this strange *feeling*.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Because it's nice and orderly. Well..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because it's nice and orderly. Well laid pallet. Easy on the eyes.
